#Agl Test Framwork

This repository stores the code of agl-test framework

##Building

Before compiling, add "agl-test" to the source option to compile
the agl-test into the image.
After that, load the compiled image onto the board.

##Running

Run the following command to execute the test set:
agl-test

Or run the test set list of the specified marker
agl-test -m marker_name

You could also directly specify the name of the test set file to run
agl-test test_file_name

##Directory Structure
The directory structure is as follows:

├── agl-test
├── conftest.py
├── LICENSE
├── plugins
│   ├── agl_test_conf.py
│   ├── agl_test_log.py
│   ├── agl_test_report.py
│   └── agl_test_utils.py
├── pytest.ini
└── README

"agl-test" is the command to start the test
"conftest.py" fixture function define
Under the "plugins" directory is a general script file
"pytest.ini" is mainly used for the selection of test sets
